The bathroom is located in the hallway, finished in neutral tones and equipped with a toilet, shower cabin, and washbasin unit.

A fixed wooden staircase with built-in storage leads to the upper floor, which is arranged as a sleeping area. The space lies beneath a pitched roof with visible white-painted beams and features a dormer window at the front. This room includes a practical custom-built wardrobe wall with a hanging section, providing additional storage space. Here, the connections for the washing machine and dryer are also located, neatly concealed from view.

